{
  "_source": "OpenID AuthZEN interop 'Todo' scenario (Rick & Morty role matrix). User directory from openid/authzen interop/authzen-todo-backend/src/directory.ts; action rules and request shapes from the todo-1.1 payload spec (interop/authzen-interop-website/docs/scenarios/todo-1.1/index.md, rendered at https://authzen-interop.net/docs/scenarios/todo-1.1/). See README.md.",
  "_deviations": [
    "Subjects use the directory's email identity (e.g. rick@the-citadel.com); the live interop authenticates via OIDC and resolves the encoded `sub` (e.g. fd1614d3-... / connector `local`) to the same identity through the directory.",
    "`can_create_todo` requests carry a resource.id ('new-todo'); the interop draft payload omits it, but AuthZEN 1.0 marks resource.id REQUIRED and the decision is role-based (id-independent).",
    "The optional empty `context: {}` shown by the interop is omitted; context is OPTIONAL in AuthZEN 1.0 and carries no information here."
  ],
  "directory": {
    "rick@the-citadel.com": ["admin", "evil_genius"],
    "morty@the-citadel.com": ["editor"],
    "summer@the-smiths.com": ["editor"],
    "beth@the-smiths.com": ["viewer"],
    "jerry@the-smiths.com": ["viewer"]
  },
  "todos": {
    "7240d0db-8ff0-41ec-98b2-34a096273b9e": "morty@the-citadel.com",
    "7240d0db-8ff0-41ec-98b2-34a096273b9f": "rick@the-citadel.com"
  },
  "rules": {
    "can_read_user": "any directory user",
    "can_read_todos": "any directory user",
    "can_create_todo": "roles intersect {admin, editor}",
    "can_update_todo": "evil_genius, or an editor who owns the todo",
    "can_delete_todo": "admin, or an editor who owns the todo"
  },
  "single": [
